<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,983,1083]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,983,1010]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Tegmina with an hexagonal cell present between veins MP and CuA (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1144,984,1010]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,913,938]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,206,884]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,198,887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Acropsis tectiformis, left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833507/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Cercus apex acute, with slightly curved triangular distal spine (
<figureCitation box="[592,683,1020,1046]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
). Lateral lobes of mesosternum with margins inward curved, with apex acute (
<figureCitation box="[285,371,1056,1082]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
